'''Sprucing up''' refers to a procedure for ensuring that a voting method satisfies the [[Condorcet Criterion]] and [[Independence of clones]].  It was described by Forest Simmons on the [[election-methods mailing list]].  See [http://lists.electorama.com/htdig.cgi/election-methods-electorama.com/2004-December/014325.html his original description] for more information.

